        <div class="detail-grid">
            
            <div class="science-card">
                <h3>The Active Compound</h3>
                <p><strong>Curcumin:</strong> This is the primary bioactive substance in turmeric. It is a polyphenol with potent anti-inflammatory properties.</p>
                
                <div class="warning-box">
                    <strong>Bioavailability Fact:</strong> Curcumin is poorly absorbed by the bloodstream on its own. To increase absorption by 2,000%, you <u>must</u> consume it with <strong>Black Pepper</strong> (which contains piperine).
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="benefits-list">
                <h3>Health Impact</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Joint Health:</strong> Reduces oxidative stress in joints, helping with recovery after exercise.</li>
                    <li><strong>Brain Function:</strong> Linked to increased levels of Brain-Derived Neurotrophic Factor (BDNF).</li>
                    <li><strong>Heart Health:</strong> Improves the function of the endothelium (the lining of your blood vessels).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

